problem: Allow users to grant Aver MCP OAuth scopes when clients omit scope requests, without embedding HTML in Rust source
approach: Added Askama templates for consent/error pages, rendered all supported scopes as checkbox options with requested scopes preselected, and persisted checked scopes into consent/code/token flow
failed_paths:
  - Initial implementation built HTML strings directly in consent.rs before user clarified template requirement
  - Repeated checkbox field names did not deserialize with serde_urlencoded, so each supported scope now has a stable field name
verification:
  - cargo test -q -p aver-server consent_
  - cargo test -q -p aver-server
  - cargo clippy -q -p aver-server --tests -- -D warnings
  - cargo fmt --all -- --check
workflow_learning: For server-rendered HTML in Rust services, choose a template crate up front and keep Rust limited to typed view models plus render calls
related_files:
  - crates/aver-server/src/consent.rs
  - crates/aver-server/templates/consent.html
  - crates/aver-server/templates/error.html
  - crates/aver-server/Cargo.toml
  - README.md
